rComments: She's very enthusiastic about the subject matter. Her lectures are packed with interesting information. She's a bit of a tough marker but you can easily approach her for help or ways to improve.

Smart, organized, passionate about material. She made a helpful webinar for us about essay writing. lots of class discussion, main ideas clear, note taking easy. I would have liked to see her deliver longer more in depth lectures. No final exam. Her points of view can be predictably feminist but she tolerates different opinions. Solid prof.

Prof Gurman's excitement for the material is contagious. She is great at creating discussion in the class, but still making sure we stay on track and notice the important themes. There is quite a bit of reading, but it is worth it. Definitely one of the best English classes I've ever had.
teacherRatingTags: ['Participation matters', "Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Amazing lectures']
